        "setup": "To use the Neartime-hosted APIs, apply for a Neartime Service account via your Experian account team. The developer guides say clients must first obtain a Neartime Service account by talking with their Experian Account Manager, then complete account setup to receive a username and password for login plus identifiers used in requests such as `SSO ID`, `client ID`, and subscribed `asset ID` values. See the [ConsumerView API Developer Guide](https://developer.experian.com/system/files/2022-03/consumerview-api-developer-guide.pdf), [Household Directory API Developer Guide](https://developer.experian.com/system/files/2021-12/household-directory-api-developer-guide_0.pdf), [Catalist API Developer Guide](https://developer.experian.com/system/files/2021-10/catalist-api-developer-guide.pdf), and [EMEA Mosaic API Developer Guide](https://developer.experian.com/system/files/2021-12/emea-mosaic-api-developer-guide.pdf)."
